lse},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"id":14453578197,"node_id":"UNLE_lADOAJaD5s6YOSeazwAAAANdgBnV","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/App-vNext/Polly/issues/events/14453578197","actor":{"login":"martincostello","id":1439341,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzkzNDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1439341?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello","html_url":"https://github.com/martincostello","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martincostello/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"unlabeled","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2024-09-30T10:31:55Z","label":{"name":"help wanted","color":"4BC938"},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/App-vNext/Polly/issues/comments/2383597689","html_url":"https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/issues/2315#issuecomment-2383597689","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/App-vNext/Polly/issues/2315","id":2383597689,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAJaD5s6OEtB5","user":{"login":"peter-csala","id":57183693,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU3MTgzNjkz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/57183693?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala","html_url":"https://github.com/peter-csala","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peter-csala/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-09-30T16:00:16Z","updated_at":"2024-09-30T16:07:42Z","body":"## The good part\r\n\r\nThis happens only if you run the test against non-release code. For release code the strategy works as expected (you will see explanation bellow):\r\n\r\n```cs\r\nvar pipeline = new ResiliencePipelineBuilder<string>()\r\n.AddHedging(new HedgingStrategyOptions<string>()\r\n{\r\n\tShouldHandle = new PredicateBuilder<string>().HandleResult(\"foo\"),\r\n\tOnHedging = _ => throw new InvalidOperationException(\"hey hi\")\r\n}).Build();\r\n\r\nawait pipeline.ExecuteAsync<string>(ct => ValueTask.FromResult<string>(\"foo\"));\r\n```\r\nwill output\r\n```none\r\nUnhandled exception. System.InvalidOperationException: hey hi\r\n   at Program.<>c.<Main>b__0_1(OnHedgingArguments`1 _)\r\n   at Polly.Hedging.Controller.TaskExecution`1.HandleOnHedgingAsync(ResilienceContext primaryContext, Int32 attemptNumber) in /_/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/TaskExecution.cs:line 150\r\n   at Polly.Hedging.Controller.TaskExecution`1.InitializeAsync[TState](HedgedTaskType type, ResilienceContext primaryContext, Func`3 primaryCallback, TState state, Int32 attemptNumber) in /_/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/TaskExecution.cs:line 127\r\n   at Polly.Hedging.Utils.HedgingExecutionContext`1.LoadExecutionAsync[TState](Func`3 primaryCallback, TState state) in /_/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/HedgingExecutionContext.cs:line 62\r\n   at Polly.Hedging.HedgingResilienceStrategy`1.ExecuteCoreAsync[TState](HedgingExecutionContext`1 hedgingContext, Func`3 callback, ResilienceContext context, TState state) in /_/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/HedgingResilienceStrategy.cs:line 72\r\n   at Polly.Hedging.HedgingResilienceStrategy`1.ExecuteCore[TState](Func`3 callback, ResilienceContext context, TState state) in /_/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/HedgingResilienceStrategy.cs:line 45\r\n   at Polly.Hedging.HedgingResilienceStrategy`1.ExecuteCore[TState](Func`3 callback, ResilienceContext context, TState state) in /_/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/HedgingResilienceStrategy.cs:line 49\r\n   at Polly.Utils.Pipeline.BridgeComponent`1.<ConvertValueTask>g__ConvertValueTaskAsync|5_0[TTo](ValueTask`1 valueTask, ResilienceContext resilienceContext) in /_/src/Polly.Core/Utils/Pipeline/BridgeComponent.TResult.cs:line 51\r\n   at Polly.ResiliencePipeline.ExecuteAsync[TResult](Func`2 callback, CancellationToken cancellationToken) in /_/src/Polly.Core/ResiliencePipeline.AsyncT.cs:line 170\r\n   ...\r\n```\r\n## The bad part\r\n\r\n### The happy path\r\n\r\nLet's amend the `OnHedging` delegate to the following:\r\n```cs\r\n_options.OnHedging = _ => default;\r\n```\r\n1. After the `OnHedging` has been successfully executed the `TaskExecution` finishes the [`HandleOnHedgingAsync`](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/main/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/TaskExecution.cs#L150) method.  \r\n2. Its caller the [`InitializeAsync`](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/main/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/TaskExecution.cs#L127) continues the execution\r\n3. Its caller the `HedgingExecutionContext`'s [`LoadExecutionAsync`](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/main/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/HedgingExecutionContext.cs#L62) continues the execution\r\n4. And the execution continues its journey inside the `HedgingResilienceStrategy`'s [`ExecuteCoreAsync`](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/main/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/HedgingResilienceStrategy.cs#L72)\r\n\r\nFinally we reach this code where we mark the `TaskExecution` as **Accepted**.\r\nhttps://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/25e57e4a4c15513f505ea484237119b2a13b31a9/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/HedgingResilienceStrategy.cs#L88-L92\r\n\r\n### The unhappy path\r\n\r\nLet's run the original `OnHedging` delegate which throws an `InvalidOperationException`\r\n\r\n1.  There is no explicit exception handling inside the `TaskExecution`'s `HandleOnHedgingAsync` and `InitializeAsync` methods so, the exception bubbles up to the`HedgingExecutionContext`\r\n2. There is no explicit exception handling inside the `HedgingExecutionContext`'s `LoadExecutionAsync` method so, the exception bubbles up to the `HedgingResilienceStrategy`\r\n3. There is no explicit exception handling inside the `ExecuteCoreAsync` **BUT** there is a `try-finally` block inside the `ExecuteCore` which is its caller\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/25e57e4a4c15513f505ea484237119b2a13b31a9/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/HedgingResilienceStrategy.cs#L43-L50\r\n\r\n 4. Inside the `finally` block we dispose the `HedgingExecutionContext`. Its [`DisposeAsync`](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/main/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/HedgingExecutionContext.cs#L76) calls the [`UpdateOriginalContext`](https://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/main/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/HedgingExecutionContext.cs#L195)\r\n 5. And since we did not have any `AcceptOutcome` calls on this execution path, that's why the test fails with a `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestPlatform.TestHost.DebugAssertException`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/App-vNext/Polly/blob/25e57e4a4c15513f505ea484237119b2a13b31a9/src/Polly.Core/Hedging/Controller/HedgingExecutionContext.cs#L202\r\n\r\nIf we comment out the `Debug.Assert` then the test passes as expected.\r\n\r\n@martintmk, @martincostello Are you guys okay to delete that assertion?","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","rea